      "@type": "CreativeWork",
      "@id": "source_BI0602_Biological_Agents_html",
      "name": "BI0602_Biological_Agents.html",
      "description": "Original UNDRR/ISC Hazard Information Profile (HIPS) page for BI0602: Biological Agents. This self-contained HTML document (base64-encoded) preserves the full authoritative content as published at https://www.preventionweb.net/understanding-disaster-risk/terminology/hips/bi0602. It includes: (1) the official SKOS concept definition with skos:prefLabel, skos:definition, skos:scopeNote, skos:broader, and skos:altLabel; (2) structured JSON-LD metadata embedded in a <script type='application/ld+json'> block; (3) thematic sections covering hazard drivers, impacts, risk metrics, multi-hazard context, monitoring/early-warning guidance, and risk management measures; (4) bibliographic references and provenance (dct:source, prov:wasQuotedFrom, prov:wasInfluencedBy). Parsing Tip: The core technical content can be extracted from the HTML structure by targeting the <article class='custom-full-content'> (or fallback <div class='main-container'>) container and decomposing boilerplate script, style, noscript, and iframe tags. Section titles follow repeated patterns: major sections use <h2> and <h3> tags with class 'field-label-above' or 'field-group-title' (e.g., 'Primary reference(s)', 'Annotations', 'Drivers', 'Impacts', 'Risk Management', 'Monitoring', 'References'), and inline field labels use <div> with class 'field--label' or 'field-label-inline' (e.g., 'Unique identifier / Notation', 'Synonyms', 'Definition'). Intended uses: AI model training on technical disaster-risk terminology, multilingual controlled-vocabulary generation, information extraction, and semantic enrichment of the UNDRR-ISC Hazard Information Profiles dataset.",
      "contentUrl": "hips/BI0602/data/distribution/BI0602_Biological_Agents.html",
      "encodingFormat": "text/html",
      "sha256": "062d4b95e9f9a94a4ea3aa2cb2899ec100131be62f90e9704a83b6d79158f744"
    },
